    {
        "content": "<p>It seems that <code>initial.to_comp_assoc</code> does not need to be a <code>simp</code> lemma. I have opted to simply not add the reassoc tag to <code>initial.to_comp</code>. PR is here: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/21527\">#21527</a></p>",
        "id": 498247591,
        "sender_full_name": "Charlie Conneen",
        "timestamp": 1738894993
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>An <code>assoc</code> version of <code>initial.to_comp</code> might still be useful though. Perhaps add the <code>assoc</code>but without taging the <code>assoc</code> as <code>simp</code>? (You can achieve this by <code>@[simp, reassoc]</code> instead of  <code>@[reassoc (attr := simp)]</code>)</p>",
        "id": 498251456,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1738897576
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, sure. Thanks for input.</p>",
